Children are among the most affected by the consequences of war &amp; armed conflict.

On Saturday's Int'l Day of Innocent Children Victims of Aggression, see how 
@UNICEF is helping protect children around the world: https://t.co/KuR4QZR6Re https://t.co/MnmcqxCzlP

Ukraine: Since the 24 February Russian invasion, 1 in 3 households have struggled with food insecurity. 

@WFP has reached millions of people with aid, but more help is needed. https://t.co/IYY1h66wiB

 https://t.co/QG6pXvmqLG

Many families around the world face serious challenges when it comes to childcare, a situation further exacerbated by #COVID19 &amp; other crises. 

@UNICEF has helpful advice for parents &amp; caregivers struggling during uncertain times.

https://t.co/85gRdlQYrU

Climate change is a primary driver of biodiversity loss. 
Yet, biodiversity is part of the solution to climate change. 

@UNBiodiversity chief @mremae explains how the two are linked and cannot be separated. https://t.co/t1pw9PgeEv

More than 3.5 million people have fled to Poland from Ukraine since the start of the war, arriving with very little.

@Refugees continues to scale up operations to provide essential health &amp; public aid services to those in need.
https://t.co/X3Sibwdbf6

Conflict, #COVID19, the climate crisis &amp; rising costs are resulting in enormous suffering for 811 million hungry people globally. 

@WFP is responding, but the gap between needs &amp; funding is bigger than ever. https://t.co/cbtdskdOSU #FightFoodCrises

 https://t.co/j0GdQdnbOv

The war in Ukraine could push 9 out of 10 people in the country into or near poverty.

Two decades of development gains are at risk.

@UNDP remains committed to the people of Ukraine &amp; will continue supporting their long-term needs. https://t.co/P2gW8oIzgL https://t.co/jzlCj8maDI
